  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I know what he feels about me?",
  "response": "Understanding someone's feelings towards you can be challenging, but there are some steps you can take to get a better sense of how he might feel:\n\n1. **Observe His Behavior**: Pay attention to how he acts around you. Does he make an effort to spend time with you? Does he remember details about your conversations and show genuine interest in your life? These can be signs of affection.\n\n2. **Body Language**: Non-verbal cues can be telling. Does he maintain eye contact, smile a lot around you, or find excuses to touch you (like a gentle touch on the arm)? These might indicate he's interested.\n\n3. **Communication**: How often does he initiate contact? Does he text or call you just to chat, or does he only reach out for specific reasons? Frequent, unprompted communication can be a good sign.\n\n4. **Listen to What He Says**: Pay attention to compliments and how he talks about the future. Does he include you in his plans? Does he talk about \"we\" instead of \"I\"?\n\n5. **Ask Directly**: If you're comfortable, the most straightforward way to know his feelings is to ask. You could say something like, \"I've really enjoyed spending time with you. How do you feel about us?\"\n\n6. **Trust Your Gut**: Sometimes, your intuition can give you a good sense of how someone feels about you. If you feel like he's into you, there's a good chance he might be.\n\n7. **Talk to Mutual Friends**: Sometimes, friends can offer insights into his feelings without him directly expressing them.\n\nRemember, everyone expresses feelings differently, and it's important to communicate openly to avoid misunderstandings. If you're unsure, it's always best to have an honest conversation about your feelings and where you stand with each other.",
